main event: An unidentified luminous object was reported in Venezuela on 13 March 1956.
interesting points: The object was larger than 5,000 meters and brighter than a star,The object was tracked by radar for over 1 hour,The object remained stationary for about 15 minutes before rapidly accelerating and disappearing,It was reported by multiple witnesses, including local people from Caracas,No sound was audible from the object.
sighted object: unidentified luminous object with a violet colored luminous atmosphere
witness description: local people and observers from Turquestein and Caracas
